# 
# http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000052
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000052> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000052> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#inverseOf> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000053> .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000052> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#FunctionalProperty> .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000052> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112> "this fragility is a characteristic of this vase"@en .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000052> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112> "this red color is a characteristic of this apple"@en .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000052> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "a relation between a specifically dependent continuant (the characteristic) and any other entity (the bearer), in which the characteristic depends on the bearer for its existence."@en .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000052> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Note that this relation was previously called \"inheres in\", but was changed to be called \"characteristic of\" because BFO2 uses \"inheres in\" in a more restricted fashion. This relation differs from BFO2:inheres_in in two respects: (1) it does not impose a range constraint, and thus it allows qualities of processes, as well as of information entities, whereas BFO2 restricts inheres_in to only apply to independent continuants (2) it is declared functional, i.e. something can only be a characteristic of one thing." .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000052> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "characteristic of"@en .
# 
# http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000053
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000053> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000053> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#InverseFunctionalProperty> .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000053> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000020> .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000053> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112> "this apple is bearer of this red color"@en .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000053> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112> "this vase is bearer of this fragility"@en .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000053> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "Inverse of characteristic_of"@en .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000053> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000116> "A bearer can have many dependents, and its dependents can exist for different periods of time, but none of its dependents can exist when the bearer does not exist."@en .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000053> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "has characteristic"@en .
