_:genid190 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000002> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "We recognize that some of the materials in the subclasses also occur naturally. However, these are not within the scope of our consideration for technical use."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000002> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "engineered material"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000002> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "An engineered material is a material that is output of a manufacturing process."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000002> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> "true"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
