<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000051> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Simulation entity role is a role that inheres in an independent continuant (IC) and is realized in a simulation process. This role enables the IC to participate in the simulation as a proxy, model, or representative of a real or hypothetical entity within the simulated context"@en .
