<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000103> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000833> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000103> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "hardening"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000103> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "toughening" .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000103> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A manufacturing process that increases the strength and hardness of a material."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000104
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000104> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000104> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000103> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000104> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "ion-exchange hardening"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000104> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Hardening process used in glass manufacturing where ions in the glass are replaced by larger ions from a solution which create compressive stress and increased hardness."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000107
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000107> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
