# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000631
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000631> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000631> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000933> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000631> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Empirische Potential MD Simulation"@de .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000631> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "empirical potential molecular dynamics simulation"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000631> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A simulation process that uses empirical potentials derived from experimental data to model the behavior of molecular systems."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000631> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Ein Simulationsprozess, der empirische Potentiale verwendet, die aus experimentellen Daten abgeleitet sind, um das Verhalten molekularer Systeme zu modellieren."@de .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000631> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "Simulating the diffusion of atoms in a crystal using Lennard-Jones potentials."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000633
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000633> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000633> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602> .
