<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000636> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000636> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000602> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000636> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> "“Extensometer.” Merriam-Webster.com Dictionary, Merriam-Webster, https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/extensometer. Accessed 5 Dec. 2022."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000636> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "extensometer"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000636> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A device for measuring minute deformations of test specimens caused by tension, compression, bending, or twisting."@en .
