<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000888> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000116> "Classified by morphology."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000888> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "polymer"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000888> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A polymer is an engineered material that consists of many repeated subunits (monomers) to form long chains. The atoms within a polymer chain are bonded together by covalent bonds. The intermolecular forces between polymer chains are typically represented by van der waals forces and hydrogen bonds."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000888> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> "true"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000889
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000889> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000889> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000635> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000889> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "pore growth"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000889> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Pore growth is an evolution of damage describing the process by which voids or pores in a material increase in size, often affecting its mechanical and physical properties."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000889> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> "true"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000890
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000890> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000890> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000027> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000890> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "connected material entity aggregate"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000890> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "An object aggregate that is a mereological sum of separate material entities, which adhere to one another through chemical bonds or physical junctions that go beyond gravity."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000890> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "the atoms of a molecule, the molecules forming the membrane of a cell, the epidermis in a human body"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000890> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> "true"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000891
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000891> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000891> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000027> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000891> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "disconnected material entity aggregate"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000891> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "An object aggregate that is a mereological sum of scattered (i.e. spatially separated) material entities, which do not adhere to one another through chemical bonds or physical junctions but, instead, relate to one another merely on grounds of metric proximity. The material entities are separated from one another through space or through other material entities that do not belong to the group."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000891> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "a heap of stones, a colony of honeybees, a group of synapses, the trees of a forest, the canopy of a forest, the fish of a shoal, a group of commuters on the subway, the patients in a hospital"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000891> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> "true"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000893
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000893> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000893> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000891> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000893> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "powder"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000893> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A powder is a dry, solid disconnected material entity aggregate composed of many very fine particles. These particles can flow freely when shaken or tilted."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000893> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> "true"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000894
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000894> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000894> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000818> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000894> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Präzisionsdrehmaschine"@de .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000894> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "precision lathe"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000894> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A precision lathe is a lathe that rotates a workpiece about an axis to perform various operations such as cutting, sanding, drilling, or deformation with extreme accuracy."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000894> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Eine Präzisionsdrehmaschine ist eine Drehmaschine, die ein Werkstück um eine Achse dreht, um verschiedene Operationen wie Schneiden, Schleifen, Bohren oder Verformung mit extremer Genauigkeit durchzuführen."@de .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000895
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000895> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000895> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000806> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000895> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> "Official definition can be found in: DIN 8593-3"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000895> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> "Offizielle Definition findet man in: DIN 8593-3"@de .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000895> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Anpressen - Einpressen"@de .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000895> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "pressing on - in"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000895> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A joining process that involves mechanically pressing one component into or onto another to create a secure fit, thereby establishing a strong mechanical connection."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000895> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Ein Füge Prozess, bei dem ein Bauteil mechanisch in oder auf ein anderes gepresst wird, um eine sichere Passung und damit eine feste mechanische Verbindung herzustellen."@de .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000895> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "Clamps, Brackets, Wedging"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000896
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000896> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000896> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000896> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#disjointWith> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000967> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000896> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The pressure is commonly measured in Pascals."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000896> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "pressure"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000896> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "an intensive quality describing the force exerted per unit area in or on a material."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000896> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> "true"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
