<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020103> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "molar proportion"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020103> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "Molar Ratio"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020103> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Molar proportion is the proportion which quantifies the entities count of the part in relation to the entities count of the whole."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020103> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "The molar ratio of hydrogen gas H2 molecules to water H2O molecules is 1/1 in the oxyhydrogen reaction. The molar ratio of oxygen molecules O2 to water molecules is 2/1.\nThe molar ratio of carbon dioxide to average atmosphere air is 420 ppm as of 2022 AD."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020103> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> "true"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
