<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020112> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020112> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "grain size distribution"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020112> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "An intensive quality describing the lower length scale object aggregate (grains) that is part of the material."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020112> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> "true"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020113
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020113> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020113> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000030> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020113> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "fluid (object)"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020113> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Fluid (object) is an object that consists of some portion of matter which bears an aggregate state that concretizes a liquid or gaseous aggregate state."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020114
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020114> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020114> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000023> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020114> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "medium role"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020114> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Medium role is a role beared by an object which implies that the object serves as an intermediary for the transmission of something else, like energy, force, or information."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020114> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "Air in the air cooling process, N2 atmosphere in a furnace cooling process, oil in a quenching process, crystal lattice in a solid state diffusion"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020115
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020115> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020115> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000891> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020115> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "aerosol"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020115> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "An aerosol is a disconnected material entity aggregate which:\n1. consists of some portion of matter whose aggregate state quality concretizes gaseous and \n2. consists of some portion of matter whose aggregate state quality concretises solid or liquid (TODO: express that this portion is also a disconnected material entity aggregate)"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020115> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> "true"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
# 
