_:genid934 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#onProperty> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000080> .
_:genid934 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#disjointWith> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020148> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "intensive quality"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "Point property"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "An intensive quality is a quality that inheres in only portion of matter and thus is independent of the bearers (system-) size."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> "true"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
_:genid935 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Axiom> .
_:genid935 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#annotatedSource> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131> .
_:genid935 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#annotatedProperty> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> .
_:genid935 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#annotatedTarget> _:genid934 .
_:genid935 <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Due to the duality of object and portion of matter this axiom can not be an equivalent class axiom."@en .
