# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020136
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020136> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020136> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000015> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020136> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The number of phases involved can vary as well as the mechanisms involved can be different."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020136> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "phase transformation"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020136> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A thermodynamic phase transformation is a process in/of a thermodynamic system, that involves the transformation of phases of the system to other phases."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020136> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> "true"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020137
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020137> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020137> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020000> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020137> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#disjointWith> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020149> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020137> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "See metastable phase"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020137> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "stable phase"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020137> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A stable phase is a phase that does not have a \"pmd:disposition of a phase to transform\" in the \"pmd:phase transformation\" it participates."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020137> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "A phase that participates in a phase transformation pt and pt that is not a metastable phase."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020137> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> "true"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020138
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020138> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020138> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#equivalentClass> <https://w3id.org/pmd/log/LOG_1000037> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020138> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000027> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020138> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "lot"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020138> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A lot is an object aggregate whose parts are output of the same production process."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020139
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020139> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020139> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020113> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020139> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Schmelze"@de .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020139> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "melt"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020139> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "is a fluid (object) with a disposition to realize a blank role in a manufacturing process"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020139> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "molten PLA in a 3D printing process"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020140
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020140> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020140> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_60003> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020140> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "portion of pure chemical element"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020140> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A portion of pure chemical element is a pure substance composed of multiple atoms, which are all of the same kind."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020141
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020141> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020141> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000015> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020141> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Fatigue is typically of interest when the change of the material affects the objects ability to fulfill its function."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020141> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "fatigue (reaction to repetitive loading)"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020141> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "fatigue is a process that affects an material entities integrity by nucleation and growing cracks."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020142
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020142> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020142> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020148> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020142> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <http://openenergy-platform.org/ontology/oeo/OEO_00000150> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020142> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "energy"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020142> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "an extensive quality of material entities which manifests as a capacity to perform work (such as causing motion or the interaction of molecules)"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020142> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> "true"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020143
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020143> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020143> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000015> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020143> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "process chain"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020143> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A process chain is a process that 'has continuant part' subprocesses S1...Sn where S1...Sn precede each other and where some object or object aggregate that are output of Sn are then input to Sn+1."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020144
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020144> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020144> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000023> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020144> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "product (chemical reaction)"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020144> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Product is the role of a material entity that is output of a chemical reaction and is created or transformed during the reaction."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020145
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020145> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020145> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000023> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020145> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "educt"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020145> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Educt is the role of a material entity that is input of a chemical reaction and is consumed or transformed during the reaction"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020146
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020146> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020146> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000023> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020146> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "catalyst"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020146> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Catalyst is the role of a participant in a chemical reaction that does not alter its qualities/realizable entities  after the chemical reaction."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020147
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020147> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020147> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020136> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020147> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "It is defined on the phase diagram at fixed composition and typically proceeds by diffusion‑controlled nucleation and growth (e.g., γ → α + Fe3C producing pearlite in steels)."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020147> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "eutectoid phase transformation"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020147> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A eutectoid phase transformation is a phase transformation in which a solid parent phase of eutectoid composition decomposes into two distinct solid daughter phases at constant temperature and pressure."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020147> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> "true"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020148
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020148> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020148> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000019> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020148> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "extensive quality"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020148> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "An extensive quality is a quality that inheres in only object or object aggregate or fiat object part or chemical entity and is dependent on the bearers (system-) size."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020148> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> "true"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020149
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020149> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020149> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020000> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020149> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The stability of a phase can only be evaluated in the context of a (possibly unknown) phase transformation process."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020149> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "metastable phase"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020149> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A metastable phase phase_trans is a phase that has a \"pmd:disposition of a phase to transform\" disp_trans and disp_trans is realized in a \"pmd:phase transformation\" proc_trans and proc_trans has participant sys_trans and sys_trans has part phase_trans."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020149> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> "true"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020150
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020150> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020150> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020132> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020150> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "volume"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020150> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Volume is a three dimensional size."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020150> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> "true"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020151
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020151> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020151> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020142> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020151> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#disjointWith> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020155> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020151> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "internal energy"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020151> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Internal energy is a universal extensive quality that specifies the bearers potential to do work."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020151> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> "true"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020152
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020152> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020152> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000027> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020152> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "component"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020152> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A component is an object aggregate that bears a function in a technical system."@en .
# 
