# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020176
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020176> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020176> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000030> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020176> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "plate"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020176> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A plate is a thick rectangular object that may bear a semi finished product role. At the same time it may be a material."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020177
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020177> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020177> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000030> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020177> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "bar"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020177> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A bar is a long object with rectangular section that may bear a semi finished product role. At the same time it may be a material."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020178
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020178> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020178> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000030> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020178> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "rod"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020178> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A rod is a long object with oval or round section that may bear a semi finished product role. At the same time it may be a material."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020179
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020179> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020179> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000030> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020179> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "This class does not include cables or other compound structures."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020179> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "wire (semi finished product)"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020179> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A wire is a long and somewhat flexible object that may bear a semi finished product role. At the same time it is a material."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020180
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020180> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020180> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000030> .
