<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020213> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "grain boundary"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020213> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A grain boundary is a fiat surface that separates adjacent grains in a polycrystalline material and is characterized by structural discontinuity."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020213> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "the part of a grain that is close to the grain boundary and possibly characterized by disorder is a fiat object part (grain surface layer)"@en .
