# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050000
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050000> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050000> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000145> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050000> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "bond"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050000> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A bond is a relational quality describing the force interaction between atoms."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050000> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> "true"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050001
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050001> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050001> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050000> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050001> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://sciencenotes.org/types-of-chemical-bonds/> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050001> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "covalent bond"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050001> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A covalent bond is a bond that forms when nonmetal atoms share electrons to achieve a stable electron configuration."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050001> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "In a water molecule (H₂O), the hydrogen and oxygen atoms share electrons."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050001> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> "true"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050002
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050002> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050002> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050000> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050002> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://www.thoughtco.com/metallic-bond-definition-properties-and-examples-4117948> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050002> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "metallic bond"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050002> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A metallic bond is a bond that forms between metal atoms, where electrons are shared in a \"sea\" of electrons that move freely around the metal ions. This type of bonding gives metals their characteristic properties such as conductivity and malleability."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050002> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> "true"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050003
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050003> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050003> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050000> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050003> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <https://sciencenotes.org/types-of-chemical-bonds/> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050003> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "ionic bond"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050003> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "An ionic bond is a bond that occurs when one atom donates an electron to another atom, resulting in oppositely charged ions that attract each other."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050003> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "An example is the interaction between the atoms of sodium chloride (NaCl), where the sodium atom donates an electron to a chlorine atom."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050003> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> "true"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
# 
