<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050050> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "glass-ceramic"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050050> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Glass‑ceramics are inorganic, non‑metallic materials prepared by controlled crystallization of glasses via different processing methods; they contain at least one type of functional crystalline phase and a residual glass, and the crystallized volume fraction may vary from ppm to almost 100%."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0050050> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "engenieered material that is inorganic, non‑metallic and prepared by controlled crystallization of glasses via different processing methods; they contain at least one type of functional crystalline phase and a residual glass, and the crystallized volume fraction may vary from ppm to almost 100%"@en .
