# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0090001
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0090001> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0090001> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000005> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0090001> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "semiconductivity"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0090001> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Semiconductivity is the disposition of a material to conduct electricity only when a certain level of excitation (via temperature, impurities, photonic excitation, electric field) elevates electrons from the valence band into the conduction band."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0090001> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000060> "true"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0090002
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0090002> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0090002> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020142> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0090002> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "band gap"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0090002> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "bandgap"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0090002> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "energy gap"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0090002> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A bandgap is an energy range between the valence band and the conduction band in a solid where no electronic states exist." .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0090002> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "Silicon has a band gap of 1.107 eV at room temperature."@en .
